Doc Johnson.

247
00:12:39.454 --> 00:12:42.631
And you. get some clean water
and a towel.

248
00:12:45.155 --> 00:12:48.637
Get your hands off me.
nigger!

249
00:12:48.680 --> 00:12:51.205
You gon' make me regret
my support. you repeat yourself.

250
00:12:51.248 --> 00:12:53.773
Mr. Fenwick.

251
00:12:54.686 --> 00:12:57.472
Louis de Pointe du Lac. sir.

252
00:12:57.515 --> 00:13:00.475
Oh. Pointe du Lac.

253
00:13:00.518 --> 00:13:03.565
Oh. forgive me. I...

254
00:13:03.608 --> 00:13:05.915
It was...
There's so much wine.

255
00:13:05.959 --> 00:13:08.875
Don't worry none.
We'll keep this here 'tween us.

256
00:13:08.918 --> 00:13:10.790
Someone got the good doc
on the way.

257
00:13:12.835 --> 00:13:17.144
Oh. Miss Williams.
Isn't she a vision?

258
00:13:17.187 --> 00:13:19.320
I ain't cleanin' his dick.

259
00:13:19.363 --> 00:13:20.538
Oh. Jesus. Mary.

260
00:13:20.582 --> 00:13:21.975
Got a situation here.
Finn.

261
00:13:22.018 --> 00:13:24.499
Yeah. well. you got another one
outside 122.

262
00:13:24.542 --> 00:13:26.501
Man acting the maggot.
driving away business.

263
00:13:26.544 --> 00:13:29.286
Ain't that what
I pay you for?

264
00:13:29.330 --> 00:13:32.028
It's a citizen priest.

265
00:13:32.072 --> 00:13:33.551
Do you not realize. sister.
your body

266
00:13:33.595 --> 00:13:35.031
is part of Christ the Lord?

267
00:13:35.075 --> 00:13:36.859
Second time this month.When you take that body

268
00:13:36.903 --> 00:13:38.513
and enjoin in harlotry
you are defiling the Lord.

269
00:13:38.556 --> 00:13:40.167
And I could give two moons if
he's your brother. Mr. du Lac.

270
00:13:40.210 --> 00:13:41.559
I'm gonna knock his skull
in the Pontchartrain!

271
00:13:41.603 --> 00:13:43.300
...you deny
your victory with Christ.

272
00:13:43.344 --> 00:13:45.694
He shall come again to judge
the living and the dead.

273
00:13:45.737 --> 00:13:47.957
And who has come and gone
then will rise again

274
00:13:48.001 --> 00:13:49.698
with their bodies
into everlasting fire.

275
00:13:49.741 --> 00:13:52.266
Go on home.
Tell Mama not to wait up.

276
00:13:52.309 --> 00:13:54.224
There's blood
on your shirt.

277
00:13:54.268 --> 00:13:55.530
What wickedness
is it tonight?

278
00:13:55.573 --> 00:13:57.184
You're not helping me here.
Paul.

279
00:13:57.227 --> 00:13:59.186
Oh. but I am.

280
00:13:59.229 --> 00:14:02.102
The Lord told me to come.
Louis.

281
00:14:02.145 --> 00:14:04.452
In my head. like a family
of birds. many voices.

282
00:14:04.495 --> 00:14:05.714
but also one voice ...

283
00:14:05.757 --> 00:14:07.324
Saying it
a second time.

284
00:14:07.368 --> 00:14:08.543
Listen to me. please.

285
00:14:08.586 --> 00:14:10.545
I'm having
a fucking night. okay?

286
00:14:10.588 --> 00:14:11.676
I can't have it
with you foo...

287
00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:13.287
[Grunts]

288
00:14:13.330 --> 00:14:16.072
[Crowd gasping]

289
00:14:16.116 --> 00:14:20.163
Get on home. else I'll bleed ya
like a kochon. bruh.

290
00:14:20.207 --> 00:14:22.731
[Crowd shouting]

291
00:14:22.774 --> 00:14:27.127
♪

292
00:14:27.170 --> 00:14:29.825
Louis: <i>Did I want to pull
a knife on my brother?</i>

293
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:31.522
<i>No.</i>

294
00:14:31.566 --> 00:14:34.264
<i>But as I alluded to before.</i>

295
00:14:34.308 --> 00:14:37.877
<i>you couldn't look weak
on Liberty.</i>

296
00:14:37.920 --> 00:14:40.531
<i>You never knew
who was watching.</i>

297
00:14:43.534 --> 00:14:46.015
[Horse neighs]

298
00:14:46.059 --> 00:14:47.799
Paul: He pulled his knife
on me. Mamaw.

299
00:14:47.843 --> 00:14:50.237
Louis: You were disrupting
mother's business interests.

300
00:14:50.280 --> 00:14:53.240
D'you hear that. Mother?
He's made you a madam.

301
00:14:53.283 --> 00:14:54.632
Oh. Paul.

302
00:14:54.676 --> 00:14:56.852
Profiting from
the damnation of souls.

303
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.985
Let's not fuss
on the particulars.

304
00:14:59.028 --> 00:15:02.684
Louis: <i>Mornings with my family
followed a pattern that year.</i>

305
00:15:02.727 --> 00:15:05.208
<i>My mother consumed herself
with preparations</i>

306
00:15:05.252 --> 00:15:07.123
<i>for my sister's wedding.</i>

307
00:15:07.167 --> 00:15:09.256
<i>while Paul
confused the dining table</i>

308
00:15:09.299 --> 00:15:11.432
<i>with a pulpit none of us
would recognize.</i>

309
00:15:11.475 --> 00:15:13.347
We should tithe that o'er
to St. Augustine's

310
00:15:13.390 --> 00:15:14.870
'fore this house
falls in on us.

311
00:15:14.914 --> 00:15:16.872
This is just
a temporary situation

312
00:15:16.916 --> 00:15:20.223
until Louis can find us
a more respectable business.

313
00:15:20.267 --> 00:15:22.312
Daddy was here.
we'd still be in sugar cane.

314
00:15:22.356 --> 00:15:24.097
Daddy was alive.
you'd still be locked up

315
00:15:24.140 --> 00:15:25.315
in that hospital
in Jackson.

316
00:15:25.359 --> 00:15:27.404
Louis.
let's not have that talk.

317
00:15:27.448 --> 00:15:30.277
A month from my wedding day.
and what do I dream about?

318
00:15:30.320 --> 00:15:32.235
Dancing in
my husband's arms?

319
00:15:32.279 --> 00:15:35.325
Children running in the yard?
No.

320
00:15:35.369 --> 00:15:37.458
I dream of what a quiet
breakfast might look like.

321
00:15:37.501 --> 00:15:40.287
Your man Levi's a Baptist.
no respect for the Holy Mother.

322
00:15:40.330 --> 00:15:41.679
Florence: Paul!

323
00:15:41.723 --> 00:15:42.985
He's gon' make your daughter
jump a broom.

324
00:15:43.029 --> 00:15:44.465
I'm sitting right here.Plenty of brooms

325
00:15:44.508 --> 00:15:46.206
down the street
at the Mayfair sisters' home.

326
00:15:46.249 --> 00:15:47.555
[Laughs]

327
00:15:47.598 --> 00:15:49.035
He's calling me
a witch. Mamaw.

328
00:15:49.078 --> 00:15:51.472
Paul de Pointe du Lac.
you walk that back.

329
00:15:51.515 --> 00:15:53.691
[Laughing]

330
00:15:53.735 --> 00:15:56.129
Daniel: <i>Your brother
sounds like a pain in the ass.</i>

331
00:15:56.172 --> 00:15:58.914
Louis:
<i>Fragile. stubborn. indulged.</i>

332
00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:00.698
<i>I'd promised our father
on his death bed</i>

333
00:16:00.742 --> 00:16:02.483
<i>to look after him.</i>

334
00:16:02.526 --> 00:16:06.400
<i>But when Paul's mind was right.
he was no burden.</i>

335
00:16:06.443 --> 00:16:10.012
<i>Point of fact. I loved him
more than anyone on earth.</i>

336
00:16:10.056 --> 00:16:12.188
<i>And our daily stroll
to St. Augustine</i>

337
00:16:12.232 --> 00:16:15.496
<i>was the measure
of a good day started.</i>

338
00:16:15.539 --> 00:16:18.716
Good morning. Paul.Paul: Good for you maybe.

339
00:16:18.760 --> 00:16:20.457
Morning. Louis.

340
00:16:20.501 --> 00:16:22.111
Pew's got a good shine.

341
00:16:22.155 --> 00:16:25.288
If it wasn't beneath you.
I'd send shoes your way.

342
00:16:25.332 --> 00:16:26.942
Nothing is beneath me.
son.

343
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.683
Paul: I'm ready. Father.

344
00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:33.601
I wanted to thank the family
for last Sunday's donation.

345
00:16:33.644 --> 00:16:36.169
Baby-sitting money.
Church calms him down some.

346
00:16:36.212 --> 00:16:37.735
Well. we're always here
for him.

347
00:16:37.779 --> 00:16:40.303
And the money goes a good way
towards the renovation.

348
00:16:40.347 --> 00:16:43.306
I want Father Matthias.
Thank you.

349
00:16:43.350 --> 00:16:45.308
You ain't got nothing
to confess to anyhow.

350
00:16:45.352 --> 00:16:47.354
Wasting
a good man's time.

351
00:16:47.397 --> 00:16:50.357
Be right there. Paul.

352
00:16:50.400 --> 00:16:52.881
I haven't seen you
in confession of late. Louis.

353
00:16:52.924 --> 00:16:55.057
[Chuckles]

354
00:16:55.101 --> 00:16:57.973
You know. you can always come
here if you're in need. son.

355
00:17:01.324 --> 00:17:05.459
Louis: <i>My business and my raised
religion were at odds.</i>

356
00:17:05.502 --> 00:17:08.288
<i>and the. uh...</i>

357
00:17:08.331 --> 00:17:11.769
<i>latencies within me. well.
I beat those back</i>

358
00:17:11.813 --> 00:17:14.946
<i>with a lie I told myself
about myself ...</i>

359
00:17:14.990 --> 00:17:17.471
<i>that I was a red-blooded son
of the South.</i>

360
00:17:17.514 --> 00:17:20.648
<i>seeking ass before absolution.</i>

361
00:17:20.691 --> 00:17:24.565
Daniel: <i>And you maintained
this delusion how exactly?</i>

362
00:17:24.608 --> 00:17:27.959
Louis: <i>A particular woman who
worked for the competition.</i>

363
00:17:28.003 --> 00:17:30.571
<i>As if rickety shacks
were a competition</i>

364
00:17:30.614 --> 00:17:33.574
<i>for Tom Anderson's
Fairplay Saloon.</i>

365
00:17:33.617 --> 00:17:36.881
Ah. Louis du Lac.
The night begins.

366
00:17:36.925 --> 00:17:39.014
Miss Carroll.
Miss Lily working tonight?

367
00:17:39.058 --> 00:17:40.624
Miss Lily's
on the terrace.

368
00:17:40.668 --> 00:17:43.932
<i>It was a palace of opulence
and splendor.</i>

369
00:17:43.975 --> 00:17:45.890
A Sazerac.
Mr. du Lac?

370
00:17:45.934 --> 00:17:47.501
That'll do fine.
Miss Carroll.

371
00:17:47.544 --> 00:17:49.633
<i>And catered to
an almost exclusively</i>

372
00:17:49.677 --> 00:17:51.461
<i>Caucasian clientele.</i>

373
00:17:51.505 --> 00:17:53.507
<i>which helped me
separate the locals</i>

374
00:17:53.550 --> 00:17:57.380
<i>from those visiting
from other southern states.</i>

375
00:17:57.424 --> 00:17:59.295
Shakin' the money tree tonight
I see.

376
00:17:59.339 --> 00:18:00.688
Mr. Anderson. sir.

377
00:18:00.731 --> 00:18:03.212
Can't see the dirt
for the dollars fallin'.

378
00:18:03.256 --> 00:18:05.910
Private game on Friday
if your datebook is free. Louis.

379
00:18:05.954 --> 00:18:09.000
Can do. Mr. Anderson.
Can do.

380
00:18:09.044 --> 00:18:15.311
♪

381
00:18:15.355 --> 00:18:21.578
♪

382
00:18:21.622 --> 00:18:24.929
Lestat: [Speaking French]

383
00:18:24.973 --> 00:18:27.584
Woman: I don't know much
what you're saying.

384
00:18:27.628 --> 00:18:29.456
But it sure sounds nice.

385
00:18:29.499 --> 00:18:32.328
"Only the impossible
can do the impossible."

386
00:18:32.372 --> 00:18:35.201
[Laughs]Miss Lily.

387
00:18:35.244 --> 00:18:38.334
Bonsoir. monsieur.
Do you speak French?

388
00:18:38.378 --> 00:18:41.337
We speak all sorts of tongues
in New Orleans.

389
00:18:41.381 --> 00:18:43.513
It's a hard table to get.
How'd you manage it?

390
00:18:43.557 --> 00:18:45.820
How'd you manage to get yourself
through the front door?

391
00:18:47.213 --> 00:18:48.388
Excuse me?

392
00:18:48.431 --> 00:18:49.737
I mean that
as a compliment.

393
00:18:49.780 --> 00:18:52.566
a man of your race
to have privileges here.

394
00:18:52.609 --> 00:18:55.830
Louis has a small empire
of his own down the street.

395
00:18:55.873 --> 00:18:56.961
[Chuckles]It gives him privileges.

396
00:18:57.005 --> 00:18:58.137
[Laughs]

397
00:18:58.180 --> 00:19:01.140
Somethin' funny
about that?

398
00:19:01.183 --> 00:19:03.272
Your name is Louis.

399
00:19:03.316 --> 00:19:05.492
Of course it's Louis.

400
00:19:05.535 --> 00:19:07.494
I didn't get your name.
fella.

401
00:19:11.672 --> 00:19:13.500
I know who you are. sir.

402
00:19:13.543 --> 00:19:16.285
You're the man who made me
buy a townhouse in the quarter.

403
00:19:16.329 --> 00:19:18.809
I owe you everything.
Please. join us.

404
00:19:21.029 --> 00:19:24.163
I know sometimes
men of my race.

405
00:19:24.206 --> 00:19:26.817
we all look alike
to you people.

406
00:19:26.861 --> 00:19:28.428
But I didn't sell you
no townhouse.

407
00:19:28.471 --> 00:19:30.734
Louis. have a seat.

408
00:19:30.778 --> 00:19:32.127
Let me explain.

409
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:35.261
New to the...
the New World. I am.

410
00:19:35.304 --> 00:19:36.697
That explains
the clothes.

411
00:19:36.740 --> 00:19:39.352
[Chuckles] A 19th-century man
at heart. yes.

412
00:19:39.395 --> 00:19:42.224
making his. uh. trans-Atlantic
journey by ship.

413
00:19:42.268 --> 00:19:45.314
planning very carefully
on settling myself upriver.

414
00:19:45.358 --> 00:19:46.663
Waiter:
The Sazerac. sir.

415
00:19:46.707 --> 00:19:48.012
Put that on my account.
thank you.

416
00:19:48.056 --> 00:19:49.797
And two more for us.

417
00:19:49.840 --> 00:19:52.060
And another round for the
musicians. whatever they want.

418
00:19:53.279 --> 00:19:54.802
Yes. sir.

419
00:19:54.845 --> 00:19:56.673
Oh. where was I?

420
00:19:56.717 --> 00:19:58.632
On a boat.

421
00:19:58.675 --> 00:20:00.373
[Chuckles]

422
00:20:04.464 --> 00:20:06.074
[Gasps]So. I'm out on

423
00:20:06.117 --> 00:20:07.902
the Crescent coast.
floating past your village.

424
00:20:07.945 --> 00:20:10.687
when I hear music playing.

425
00:20:10.731 --> 00:20:14.996
and the shadows of men and women
dancing by the water's edge.

426
00:20:15.039 --> 00:20:20.349
I disembarked for the music.
but then there was the food.

427
00:20:20.393 --> 00:20:22.133
What's been your favorite
this year. Mr. Lioncourt?

428
00:20:22.177 --> 00:20:23.439
A favorite?

429
00:20:23.483 --> 00:20:24.701
Mm.
Mm.

430
00:20:24.745 --> 00:20:27.574
She puts a pistol
to my head.

431
00:20:27.617 --> 00:20:30.185
Louis:
<i>I couldn't believe it.</i>

432
00:20:30.229 --> 00:20:32.187
<i>Staring me down as his hands</i>

433
00:20:32.231 --> 00:20:36.017
<i>went wandering the seams
of Miss Lily's dress.</i>

434
00:20:36.060 --> 00:20:37.671
I wanted to take the end
of my cane

435
00:20:37.714 --> 00:20:40.369
and slit his throat
with it.

436
00:20:40.413 --> 00:20:43.198
Daniel: Why didn't you?

437
00:20:43.242 --> 00:20:45.244
I couldn't move.

438
00:20:45.287 --> 00:20:48.986
<i>My body was seized
with weakness.</i>

439
00:20:49.030 --> 00:20:54.905
<i>His gaze tied a string
around my lungs.</i>

440
00:20:54.949 --> 00:20:58.257
<i>and I found myself
immobilized.</i>

441
00:20:58.300 --> 00:21:02.783
And the women.
all shades of skin ...

442
00:21:02.826 --> 00:21:07.309
white. Black. cinnamon.

443
00:21:07.353 --> 00:21:10.486
I've emptied a bank vault
sampling. I must say.

444
00:21:10.530 --> 00:21:13.750
But it was not until
a few nights later...

445
00:21:21.889 --> 00:21:25.719
...that I said to myself...

446
00:21:25.762 --> 00:21:27.416
"Lestat. unpack your trunks.

447
00:21:27.460 --> 00:21:29.418
You're home."
[Laughs]

448
00:21:30.593 --> 00:21:33.509
What did he say
just now?

449
00:21:33.553 --> 00:21:35.511
A little more
than he should of.

450
00:21:35.555 --> 00:21:39.602
I had planned to make a new life
for myself in St. Louis.

451
00:21:39.646 --> 00:21:43.171
That was to be my destiny.

452
00:21:43.214 --> 00:21:46.043
And now I know I was right.

453
00:21:46.087 --> 00:21:48.045
Only it turns out the saint
is not a city.

454
00:21:48.089 --> 00:21:53.573
but a handsome man with
a most agreeable disposition.

455
00:21:53.616 --> 00:21:56.489
You're his destiny.
Louis.

456
00:21:56.532 --> 00:21:58.491
Destined to be
very good friends.

457
00:22:00.667 --> 00:22:02.843
The Orient room is available
for the next few hours.

458
00:22:02.886 --> 00:22:04.192
Miss Lily.

459
00:22:04.235 --> 00:22:05.628
The gentlemen
are swappin'

460
00:22:05.672 --> 00:22:07.674
andouille sausage recipes.
Miss Carroll.

461
00:22:07.717 --> 00:22:09.284
Hmm.

462
00:22:09.328 --> 00:22:17.336
♪

463
00:22:17.379 --> 00:22:20.164
[Indistinct chatter]

464
00:22:24.691 --> 00:22:27.084
Carroll: The Orient room
is yours. monsieur.

465
00:22:27.128 --> 00:22:29.565
Lestat: Please get my friend
here anything he wants.

466
00:22:29.609 --> 00:22:30.914
Wonderful to meet you.

467
00:22:30.958 --> 00:22:34.396
I do hope I run into you again.
Louis.

468
00:22:34.440 --> 00:22:39.445
Louis: <i>Emasculation and
admiration in equal measure.</i>

469
00:22:40.402 --> 00:22:45.059
I wanted to murder the man.
and I wanted to be the man.

470
00:22:49.629 --> 00:22:52.501
I had come there for Lily.

471
00:22:52.545 --> 00:22:55.199
But I left thinking of only him.

472
00:22:56.505 --> 00:22:58.159
[Foghorn blows]

473
00:22:58.202 --> 00:23:01.075
Lamplighter:
[Singing in French]

474
00:23:05.166 --> 00:23:09.039
[Singing in French]

475
00:23:17.091 --> 00:23:20.703
[Singing continues]

476
00:23:31.366 --> 00:23:33.020
[Singing stops]

477
00:23:35.109 --> 00:23:37.285
Come now.

478
00:23:40.027 --> 00:23:41.637
Who the devil...

479
00:23:41.681 --> 00:23:49.123
♪

480
00:23:49.166 --> 00:23:51.081
[Growls]

481
00:23:51.125 --> 00:23:53.432
[Screaming]

482
00:23:56.260 --> 00:23:57.392
Our friends in the police
tell me

483
00:23:57.436 --> 00:24:00.090
there's an outbreak of fever
in town.

484
00:24:00.134 --> 00:24:02.571
It's unfortunates
living near the wharf. mostly.

485
00:24:02.615 --> 00:24:04.530
If you find yourself
riverside of Decatur...

486
00:24:04.573 --> 00:24:07.097
[Knocking]...you have only yourself
to blame. I say.

487
00:24:07.141 --> 00:24:08.490
Agreed.

488
00:24:08.534 --> 00:24:10.318
Still. very peculiar.
they say.

489
00:24:10.361 --> 00:24:13.190
Each one the same ...
small wounds to the body.

490
00:24:13.234 --> 00:24:17.760
and upon examination.
entirely devoid of blood.

491
00:24:17.804 --> 00:24:19.806
It is their theory
some new kind of rat

492
00:24:19.849 --> 00:24:21.068
has come ashore.

493
00:24:21.111 --> 00:24:23.766
Of the six-foot variety.

494
00:24:23.810 --> 00:24:26.334
We call those bureaucrats
in France.

495
00:24:26.377 --> 00:24:29.206
[Laughter]

496
00:24:29.250 --> 00:24:33.602
Gentlemen. well. you all know
Louis du Lac.

497
00:24:33.646 --> 00:24:37.301
Louis. let me introduce you
to Mr. Lestat de Lioncourt.

498
00:24:37.345 --> 00:24:39.260
We met already.
Mr. Anderson. sir.

499
00:24:39.303 --> 00:24:41.567
In front of a florist.
wasn't it?

500
00:24:41.610 --> 00:24:44.265
We both wanted
the last bouquet of lilies.

501
00:24:46.485 --> 00:24:48.791
Aren't you gonna ask the
alderman how his head is. Louis?

502
00:24:48.835 --> 00:24:51.620
Now. why would I do that.
Mr. Anderson. sir?

503
00:24:51.664 --> 00:24:54.754
You see. Mr. Fenwick.
just as I told you.

504
00:24:54.797 --> 00:24:56.712
a most discreet Negro.

505
00:24:56.756 --> 00:24:59.933
Would that his doctor
had the same standards.

506
00:24:59.976 --> 00:25:01.848
Gentlemen.
show your cards.

507
00:25:04.633 --> 00:25:07.027
Hoo!
Mr. Lioncourt.

508
00:25:07.070 --> 00:25:09.595
your hand
is incomprehensible.

509
00:25:09.638 --> 00:25:12.467
[Laughter]Oh. yes.

510
00:25:12.511 --> 00:25:14.164
I'm terrible at cards.

511
00:25:14.208 --> 00:25:16.515
Did I not mention that
to everyone?

512
00:25:16.558 --> 00:25:20.127
Would you mind. uh. getting me
some more of these money chips?

513
00:25:20.170 --> 00:25:22.303
[Laughter]

514
00:25:22.346 --> 00:25:25.741
Tom: Louis. did you know
that Alderman Fenwick here

515
00:25:25.785 --> 00:25:27.874
recently purchased
both the title and deed

516
00:25:27.917 --> 00:25:29.702
to the Horton rooming house
on Villere Street?

517
00:25:29.745 --> 00:25:31.399
Yeah. Mr. Anderson believes
it could make

518
00:25:31.442 --> 00:25:33.009
a fine sportin' house.

519
00:25:33.053 --> 00:25:35.925
I recommended the alderman
find a managing partner

520
00:25:35.969 --> 00:25:37.536
before he commits his money.

521
00:25:37.579 --> 00:25:40.060
I recommended
he think of you. Louis.

522
00:25:40.103 --> 00:25:42.541
Very kind of you.
Mr. Anderson. sir.

523
00:25:42.584 --> 00:25:45.152
Fenwick: What do you think
of the location?

524
00:25:45.195 --> 00:25:47.241
It ain't Basin Street.

525
00:25:47.284 --> 00:25:49.722
But throw enough Edison bulbs
on the facade.

526
00:25:49.765 --> 00:25:51.288
get a good margin
on the alcohol.

527
00:25:51.332 --> 00:25:53.421
no-nonsense madam
to keep the girls clean.

528
00:25:53.464 --> 00:25:55.423
I reckon a man
could make a decent sum.

529
00:25:55.466 --> 00:25:57.164
Yes. sir.
Mr. Fenwick. sir.

530
00:25:57.207 --> 00:25:59.775
I said you'd do it
for 10 percent.

531
00:25:59.819 --> 00:26:02.256
[Chuckles] A-all respects.
Mr. Anderson.

532
00:26:02.299 --> 00:26:05.433
but you proposing 10 percent
for all the work?

533
00:26:05.476 --> 00:26:07.914
15%?

534
00:26:07.957 --> 00:26:10.394
There's capital
investment.

535
00:26:10.438 --> 00:26:12.919
and there's labor.

536
00:26:12.962 --> 00:26:14.790
Both has its seat
at the table.

537
00:26:14.834 --> 00:26:16.923
Wouldn't you say.
Mr. Lestat?

538
00:26:19.099 --> 00:26:21.492
Well. I can only speak
of my experience.

539
00:26:21.536 --> 00:26:23.669
which is. I'm sure.
different in my country.

540
00:26:23.712 --> 00:26:26.367
<i>Par exemple.</i>you fine gentlemen
have heard of the success story

541
00:26:26.410 --> 00:26:29.936
that is Le Bon Marché. shopping
experience like no other.

542
00:26:29.979 --> 00:26:31.502
Aristide Boucicaut
invests in a new vision...

543
00:26:31.546 --> 00:26:33.374
Lestat:
<i>These men look down on you.</i>

544
00:26:33.417 --> 00:26:36.812
<i>I have to say. I find it
appalling how men like yourself</i>

545
00:26:36.856 --> 00:26:39.119
<i>are treated
in this country of yours.</i>

546
00:26:39.162 --> 00:26:41.948
It is undeniable.
I came to my wealth honestly

547
00:26:41.991 --> 00:26:43.602
and at great sacrifice.
I might add.

548
00:26:43.645 --> 00:26:45.778
However. it was not
the sacrifice of many.

549
00:26:45.821 --> 00:26:47.562
I had no partners
in my various...

550
00:26:47.606 --> 00:26:49.695
-Lestat: <i>10 percent.</i>
-The financial risks...

551
00:26:49.738 --> 00:26:52.132
<i>15 percent.</i>

552
00:26:54.961 --> 00:26:58.312
<i>Do you not know your value?</i>

553
00:27:01.445 --> 00:27:05.493
<i>Do you suffer these indignities
for some larger purpose?</i>

554
00:27:05.536 --> 00:27:12.892
♪

555
00:27:12.935 --> 00:27:15.808
<i>And do you think two pair
will win the hour?</i>

556
00:27:21.944 --> 00:27:25.556
I believe there is great
opportunity in this city.

557
00:27:25.600 --> 00:27:30.083
but to seize it. I'll need
protection from the wolves.

558
00:27:30.126 --> 00:27:37.568
♪

559
00:27:37.612 --> 00:27:45.098
♪

560
00:27:45.141 --> 00:27:46.316
And that's all to say.

561
00:27:46.360 --> 00:27:48.014
forgive me.
Mr. de Pointe du Lac.

562
00:27:48.057 --> 00:27:49.624
for my bias.
but where is the business

563
00:27:49.668 --> 00:27:50.973
if there is no capital?

564
00:27:51.017 --> 00:27:52.714
It does not exist. No?Alright. boys.

565
00:27:52.758 --> 00:27:54.194
Show 'em.

566
00:27:57.458 --> 00:27:59.286
Ooh.

567
00:27:59.329 --> 00:28:02.376
Full boat. Mr. du Lac.

568
00:28:02.419 --> 00:28:04.987
Got you beat. Tom.

569
00:28:05.031 --> 00:28:07.207
Louis: <i>He wouldn't tell me
how he did it.</i>

570
00:28:07.250 --> 00:28:10.123
<i>his trick
to make the world stop.</i>

571
00:28:10.166 --> 00:28:12.603
<i>"In time. Louis.
Patience. Louis.</i>

572
00:28:12.647 --> 00:28:14.954
<i>Ask me next week. Louis."</i>

573
00:28:14.997 --> 00:28:16.390
Daniel:
<i>You started hanging out?</i>

574
00:28:16.433 --> 00:28:18.044
Louis:
<i>He was in love with my city</i>

575
00:28:18.087 --> 00:28:20.786
<i>and wanted to know
everything he could about it.</i>

576
00:28:20.829 --> 00:28:24.180
Daniel: <i>So you played docent
to the gentleman vampire?</i>

577
00:28:24.224 --> 00:28:27.793
Louis: <i>He had not revealed
his vampire nature yet.</i>

578
00:28:27.836 --> 00:28:29.882
I'm assuming
you only met at night.

579
00:28:29.925 --> 00:28:31.622
It's New Orleans.

580
00:28:31.666 --> 00:28:34.495
Days are for sleeping off
the previous evening's damage.

581
00:28:34.538 --> 00:28:36.410
Perfect cover
for a vampire.

582
00:28:36.453 --> 00:28:38.847
Racing ahead again.
Mr. Molloy.

583
00:28:38.891 --> 00:28:42.329
Let the tale seduce you.

584
00:28:42.372 --> 00:28:44.723
Just as I was seduced.

585
00:28:46.420 --> 00:28:48.857
<i>Money would arrive.
wired from France.</i>

586
00:28:48.901 --> 00:28:51.555
<i>and the shopkeepers. who would
usually close at sunset.</i>

587
00:28:51.599 --> 00:28:54.428
<i>were very happy
to accommodate him.</i>

588
00:28:54.471 --> 00:28:58.519
<i>He ransacked the import houses
to furnish his town house.</i>

589
00:28:58.562 --> 00:29:01.000
<i>ravaged the booksellers
of their oldest volumes</i>

590
00:29:01.043 --> 00:29:02.566
<i>for a library.</i>

591
00:29:02.610 --> 00:29:06.657
<i>and. with encouragement.
updated his wardrobe</i>

592
00:29:06.701 --> 00:29:09.573
<i>to the fashion trends
of the season.</i>

593
00:29:09.617 --> 00:29:14.796
<i>It was a cold winter that year.
and Lestat was my coal fire.</i>

594
00:29:14.840 --> 00:29:17.494
<i>And I found myself
for the very first time.</i>

595
00:29:17.538 --> 00:29:19.627
<i>to anyone other than Paul.</i>

596
00:29:19.670 --> 00:29:22.630
<i>confiding my struggles
to another man.</i>

597
00:29:25.938 --> 00:29:29.202
<i>I was being hunted.</i>

598
00:29:29.245 --> 00:29:32.640
<i>And I was completely unaware
it was happening.</i>

599
00:29:37.993 --> 00:29:40.300
Louis: I'm switchin' rooms.
I don't need to hear you

600
00:29:40.343 --> 00:29:41.649
and your good man making noise.

601
00:29:41.692 --> 00:29:43.172
Grace: You'd have to be home
to hear that.

602
00:29:43.216 --> 00:29:45.392
I come home nights.You come home some nights.

603
00:29:45.435 --> 00:29:47.742
Out cattin' with some
white man. I hear.

604
00:29:47.786 --> 00:29:49.178
He ain't white.
he French.

605
00:29:49.222 --> 00:29:51.790
Oh. That's a new kind
of white. is it?

606
00:29:51.833 --> 00:29:53.052
French white?

607
00:29:53.095 --> 00:29:54.401
He different.

608
00:29:54.444 --> 00:29:56.403
Invite him over for dinner.

609
00:29:56.446 --> 00:29:58.492
Mother loves European.

610
00:29:58.535 --> 00:30:01.016
I'm gon' tell Levi
you fishin' for a richer man.

611
00:30:01.060 --> 00:30:03.758
Don't.
Don't deny your sister.

612
00:30:03.802 --> 00:30:05.978
I wanna meet
this French white.

613
00:30:06.021 --> 00:30:08.110
[Indistinct talking]

614
00:30:08.154 --> 00:30:10.025
I'm just trying to give you
the word of the Lord.

615
00:30:10.069 --> 00:30:13.986
Understa... Yes. Yes. No.
That is never my ...

616
00:30:14.029 --> 00:30:16.771
Paul crawled up on my bed
last night.

617
00:30:16.815 --> 00:30:19.339
[Paul continues indistinctly]

618
00:30:22.995 --> 00:30:25.519
Wept for good near
an hour.

619
00:30:25.562 --> 00:30:27.521
He ain't takin' it.
you gettin' married.

620
00:30:29.958 --> 00:30:33.832
Levi told me of a place
over in Gretna.

621
00:30:33.875 --> 00:30:35.877
takes in men like Paul.

622
00:30:35.921 --> 00:30:37.183
It's not some
crazy person's house like ...

623
00:30:37.226 --> 00:30:39.141
How'd that work
last time. huh?

624
00:30:39.185 --> 00:30:41.361
He come out
worse than before.

625
00:30:41.404 --> 00:30:44.320
Gretna.
It ain't happenin'.

626
00:30:44.364 --> 00:30:46.061
He died on the cross for you.

627
00:30:46.105 --> 00:30:47.671
Yes...you.

628
00:30:47.715 --> 00:30:49.151
I worry.

629
00:30:49.195 --> 00:30:52.981
I worry so much ...Worry about your own life.

630
00:30:53.025 --> 00:30:55.810
Worry about
being a bride.

631
00:30:57.029 --> 00:31:00.032
Worry about
what you gon' wear

632
00:31:00.075 --> 00:31:04.863
in London. in Paris.
Florence.

633
00:31:04.906 --> 00:31:06.821
Now. y'all gon' be in steerage
outta New York.

634
00:31:06.865 --> 00:31:08.475
but once you get to Europe.

635
00:31:08.518 --> 00:31:10.564
it's first class on boats.
trains. and hotel rooms.

636
00:31:10.607 --> 00:31:12.871
What did you go and do?
[Laughs]

637
00:31:12.914 --> 00:31:14.481
You should put the band
by the deck

638
00:31:14.524 --> 00:31:17.136
and the food
by the fountain.

639
00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:20.574
[Laughs]

640
00:31:21.967 --> 00:31:23.838
Mamaw!

641
00:31:23.882 --> 00:31:26.493
I'm goin' 'round the world!
[Laughs]

642
00:31:26.536 --> 00:31:28.451
♪

643
00:31:28.495 --> 00:31:31.759
[Door opens. closes]

644
00:31:35.763 --> 00:31:38.461
I can't thank you enough.
Mama du Lac.

645
00:31:38.505 --> 00:31:39.767
I never been east of Alabama.

646
00:31:39.810 --> 00:31:41.812
and now I'm going
to see the pyramids.

647
00:31:41.856 --> 00:31:45.816
Oh. I think every young family
deserves a little adventure.

648
00:31:45.860 --> 00:31:47.644
Wouldn't you say.
Monsieur Lioncourt?

649
00:31:47.688 --> 00:31:49.211
Oui. Madame.

650
00:31:49.255 --> 00:31:52.084
My mother. she gave me
every advantage in life

651
00:31:52.127 --> 00:31:53.476
as a young man.

652
00:31:53.520 --> 00:31:56.740
My first Mastiff.
first flintlock rifle.

653
00:31:56.784 --> 00:31:58.264
the means
to make my way to Paris.

654
00:31:58.307 --> 00:32:00.831
It was Louis that purchased
your holiday. Levi.

655
00:32:00.875 --> 00:32:02.094
It's Louis
who controls the money.

656
00:32:02.137 --> 00:32:03.399
Pay no mind. Levi.

657
00:32:03.443 --> 00:32:04.444
And I don't know
who gave you the right

658
00:32:04.487 --> 00:32:05.532
to call our mother
your mother.

659
00:32:05.575 --> 00:32:06.881
She's not your mother yet

660
00:32:06.925 --> 00:32:08.839
and will never be
your scientific mother.

661
00:32:08.883 --> 00:32:11.973
Florence: Paul.

662
00:32:12.017 --> 00:32:13.932
I do love
this bouillabaisse.

663
00:32:13.975 --> 00:32:16.586
Wha?

664
00:32:16.630 --> 00:32:18.719
Down here.
we call it gumbo.

665
00:32:18.762 --> 00:32:20.590
We had a gumbo the other night.
didn't we. Louis?

666
00:32:20.634 --> 00:32:22.114
Uh. right after the opera.

667
00:32:22.157 --> 00:32:23.942
Oh. we've got Louis
to an opera.

668
00:32:23.985 --> 00:32:26.553
"Iolanta."'Bout some blind princess.

669
00:32:26.596 --> 00:32:28.903
didn't know
she was a princess.

670
00:32:28.947 --> 00:32:31.123
Stomach got grumbling.
left halfway through.

671
00:32:31.166 --> 00:32:33.386
And what exactly is the nature
of your relationship

672
00:32:33.429 --> 00:32:35.954
with my brother.
Monsieur Lioncourt?

673
00:32:42.699 --> 00:32:45.137
Your brother and I
have been discussing

674
00:32:45.180 --> 00:32:47.530
a few investment
opportunities.

675
00:32:47.574 --> 00:32:50.185
The birds asked me
to ask you.

676
00:32:50.229 --> 00:32:51.839
I wasn't being rude.

677
00:32:54.494 --> 00:32:56.539
Monsieur Freniere.
would you tell me

678
00:32:56.583 --> 00:32:59.455
how you came to propose
to this delightsome young woman?

679
00:32:59.499 --> 00:33:00.848
Oh. that's a good yarn.

680
00:33:00.891 --> 00:33:03.111
Are you one with Christ.
Mr. Lioncourt?

681
00:33:03.155 --> 00:33:05.853
How 'bout you shut
your damn mouth?

682
00:33:05.896 --> 00:33:07.681
Florence: Louis.That's alright.

683
00:33:07.724 --> 00:33:10.162
Louis. Madame.
the birds speak for him.

684
00:33:13.426 --> 00:33:16.298
I came to know Christ
in a monastery.

685
00:33:18.648 --> 00:33:21.521
I wanted to be a priest.

686
00:33:21.564 --> 00:33:24.437
Just like you. Paul.

687
00:33:24.480 --> 00:33:26.917
And under the guidance
and discipline of the monks

688
00:33:26.961 --> 00:33:31.183
who lived there. I came
to memorize both the testaments.

689
00:33:31.226 --> 00:33:33.185
the writings of Assisi.

690
00:33:33.228 --> 00:33:38.016
Aquinas. Erasmus.
all the saints and scholars.

691
00:33:41.889 --> 00:33:48.287
My father. a vulgar man. did not
think much of this education.

692
00:33:48.330 --> 00:33:53.031
and so he and my brothers
conspired to pull me out.

693
00:33:53.074 --> 00:33:56.556
lock me away.
where. between beatings.

694
00:33:56.599 --> 00:33:59.254
starvations.
and the failure of Christ

695
00:33:59.298 --> 00:34:01.474
to intercede the beatings
and starvations.

696
00:34:01.517 --> 00:34:05.304
I slowly forgot all about
the testaments. Assisi.

697
00:34:05.347 --> 00:34:07.697
Aquinas. Erasmus. all of it.

698
00:34:07.741 --> 00:34:09.264
Stop.And so to answer

699
00:34:09.308 --> 00:34:11.136
your boring question.
there is an ocean

700
00:34:11.179 --> 00:34:13.138
between Christ and myself.Stop!

701
00:34:16.706 --> 00:34:18.708
Don't do that shit here!

702
00:34:21.189 --> 00:34:23.539
Not with my family.

703
00:34:23.583 --> 00:34:25.715
You understand?

704
00:34:33.854 --> 00:34:38.685
I am cursed with my father's
temper at times.

705
00:34:38.728 --> 00:34:40.861
and the rudeness is all mine.

706
00:34:40.904 --> 00:34:42.297
Florence:
That's alright.

707
00:34:42.341 --> 00:34:44.865
It's the humidity.
It does that sometimes.

708
00:34:44.908 --> 00:34:46.475
Why don't we have
some ice wine?

709
00:34:46.519 --> 00:34:47.737
[Bell ringing]

710
00:34:47.781 --> 00:34:50.262
And Levi here can tell us
all again

711
00:34:50.305 --> 00:34:53.395
how he won
my joychild's heart.

712
00:34:57.182 --> 00:35:02.404
I fear your family has taken
a permanent offense at me.

713
00:35:02.448 --> 00:35:04.014
When Paul
ain't pickin' at his plate.

714
00:35:04.058 --> 00:35:05.668
he pickin' a fight.

715
00:35:05.712 --> 00:35:08.323
If I had your tricks.
I'd have done the same.

716
00:35:08.367 --> 00:35:10.064
You must envy him.

717
00:35:10.108 --> 00:35:12.501
The boy thinks God speaks to him
through birds in his head.

718
00:35:12.545 --> 00:35:14.242
How you figure envy?

719
00:35:14.286 --> 00:35:16.288
The liberty he has
with his thoughts.

720
00:35:16.331 --> 00:35:17.854
However misshapen
they may be.

721
00:35:17.898 --> 00:35:19.943
your brother has no shame
in sharing them.

722
00:35:19.987 --> 00:35:21.815
You sayin' I got shame?

723
00:35:21.858 --> 00:35:24.644
The lie you told about leaving
the opera house early.

724
00:35:24.687 --> 00:35:26.689
You were near weeping
when the curtain fell.

725
00:35:26.733 --> 00:35:28.648
Why hide that
from your family?

726
00:35:28.691 --> 00:35:30.911
Don't everybody need
to know what I do.

727
00:35:30.954 --> 00:35:32.739
Dishonesty
breeds dishonesty.

728
00:35:32.782 --> 00:35:34.567
They sit in judgment.

729
00:35:34.610 --> 00:35:36.482
Paul is the only one
to say it to my face.

730
00:35:36.525 --> 00:35:39.006
but I know my ma
and Grace think it. too.

731
00:35:39.049 --> 00:35:41.269
My daddy ran our sugar business
into a swamp.

732
00:35:41.313 --> 00:35:44.577
When he passed.
we was four months ...

733
00:35:44.620 --> 00:35:48.450
four months from going bankrupt
if I didn't do something.

734
00:35:48.494 --> 00:35:50.974
You don't need to defend
yourself to me. Louis.

735
00:35:51.018 --> 00:35:52.802
I know what you go through
to keep your family

736
00:35:52.846 --> 00:35:54.282
ignorant in their comfort.

737
00:35:54.326 --> 00:35:56.676
It ain't easy.
the work I do.

738
00:35:56.719 --> 00:35:58.373
Nothing but broken souls
around me.

739
00:35:58.417 --> 00:36:01.550
and the ones that ain't broke
are greedy.

740
00:36:01.594 --> 00:36:04.249
Bone-tired.

741
00:36:04.292 --> 00:36:06.381
Drink up. my good man.

742
00:36:06.425 --> 00:36:08.296
The Earth's a savage garden.

743
00:36:13.562 --> 00:36:16.783
You did good gettin' off
that boat when you did.

744
00:36:16.826 --> 00:36:19.960
St. Louis
is dull as dishwater.

745
00:36:20.003 --> 00:36:24.007
Yes.
I feel quite at home here.

746
00:36:24.051 --> 00:36:26.575
Shall we have a nightcap?

747
00:36:26.619 --> 00:36:29.012
Um...

748
00:36:29.056 --> 00:36:31.319
Probably had enough
for tonight.

749
00:36:31.363 --> 00:36:33.756
Gotta make my rounds
back on Liberty.

750
00:36:33.800 --> 00:36:35.889
You must. Louis.

751
00:36:35.932 --> 00:36:38.631
I bought you a gift.

752
00:36:38.674 --> 00:36:40.894
A gift?

753
00:36:40.937 --> 00:36:42.548
A flower.

754
00:36:42.591 --> 00:36:49.772
♪

755
00:36:49.816 --> 00:36:56.997
♪

756
00:36:57.040 --> 00:37:04.309
♪

757
00:37:04.352 --> 00:37:07.921
[Music box playing]

758
00:37:07.964 --> 00:37:10.967
♪

759
00:37:11.011 --> 00:37:13.361
That's a nice music box
you got there.

760
00:37:13.405 --> 00:37:14.797
It's one of the few things
I brought with me

761
00:37:14.841 --> 00:37:17.583
from the continent.

762
00:37:17.626 --> 00:37:19.324
What's that
lil' song playin'?

763
00:37:19.367 --> 00:37:21.239
Do you like it?

764
00:37:21.282 --> 00:37:25.286
I composed it for a young
violinist I once knew.

765
00:37:25.330 --> 00:37:28.028
a boy of infinite beauty
and sensitivity.

766
00:37:34.382 --> 00:37:36.471
I believe that is for the lips.
Miss Lily.

767
00:37:36.515 --> 00:37:39.779
I don't like the way mine
look plain.

768
00:37:39.822 --> 00:37:41.911
And Mr. du Lac
don't mind when I do it.

769
00:37:41.955 --> 00:37:43.652
Mm-hmm.

770
00:37:43.696 --> 00:37:46.873
A pair of
misfit beauties.

771
00:37:46.916 --> 00:37:50.268
I can see why you both run
to the other.

772
00:37:50.311 --> 00:37:53.009
Miss Carroll know you're here.
Lily?

773
00:37:53.053 --> 00:37:54.446
I can assure you.
the Fairplay has been

774
00:37:54.489 --> 00:37:58.667
handsomely compensated
for the evening.

775
00:37:58.711 --> 00:38:01.279
Sent a two-horse carriage
to pick me up.

776
00:38:01.322 --> 00:38:03.281
Felt like the queen
of the quarter.

777
00:38:07.285 --> 00:38:11.593
I told Mr. Lioncourt.
you and me usually just talk.

778
00:38:11.637 --> 00:38:13.595
And why is that. Louis?

779
00:38:13.639 --> 00:38:17.425
What kind of a man
wastes this waist with words?

780
00:38:17.469 --> 00:38:19.122
A beautiful man.

781
00:38:23.866 --> 00:38:26.129
There's nothing to be
nervous about.

782
00:38:26.173 --> 00:38:30.395
The curtains are closed.
the servants sent home.

783
00:38:30.438 --> 00:38:33.485
Even the planets and stars
are blindfolded.

784
00:38:33.528 --> 00:38:36.749
That's your thing. then?
You like to watch?

785
00:38:39.012 --> 00:38:42.015
Lestat: <i>I've been watching you
for some time now. Louis.</i>

786
00:38:42.058 --> 00:38:45.497
<i>From river to lake.
lake back to river.</i>

787
00:38:45.540 --> 00:38:47.586
<i>looking for
my companion heart.</i>

788
00:38:47.629 --> 00:38:48.978
How you do that?

789
00:38:49.022 --> 00:38:49.979
Do what?

790
00:38:50.023 --> 00:38:51.764
<i>Do what?</i>

791
00:38:51.807 --> 00:38:54.114
Get in my head
like that.

792
00:38:54.157 --> 00:38:56.551
<i>Such a pretty head.</i>

793
00:38:56.595 --> 00:38:59.772
♪

794
00:38:59.815 --> 00:39:01.600
[Moans]

795
00:39:01.643 --> 00:39:09.912
♪

796
00:39:09.956 --> 00:39:12.785
[Breathing heavily]

797
00:39:12.828 --> 00:39:20.706
♪

798
00:39:20.749 --> 00:39:28.583
♪

799
00:39:28.627 --> 00:39:36.417
♪

800
00:39:36.461 --> 00:39:44.251
♪

801
00:39:44.294 --> 00:39:47.297
That's fine. love.

802
00:39:47.341 --> 00:39:56.568
♪

803
00:40:01.877 --> 00:40:08.884
♪

804
00:40:08.928 --> 00:40:12.714
Ah. Ah.

805
00:40:12.758 --> 00:40:15.630
[Shudders]

806
00:40:15.674 --> 00:40:24.639
♪

807
00:40:24.683 --> 00:40:33.474
♪

808
00:40:33.518 --> 00:40:42.352
♪

809
00:40:42.396 --> 00:40:51.318
♪

810
00:40:51.361 --> 00:40:53.146
[Breathing heavily]

811
00:40:53.189 --> 00:41:02.721
♪

812
00:41:02.764 --> 00:41:12.382
♪

813
00:41:12.426 --> 00:41:22.001
♪

814
00:41:22.044 --> 00:41:31.663
♪

815
00:41:33.055 --> 00:41:35.928
It bears repeating.
I did not consider myself

816
00:41:35.971 --> 00:41:38.191
a homosexual man at the time.

817
00:41:39.235 --> 00:41:41.934
I mean.
I had had experiences.

818
00:41:41.977 --> 00:41:44.589
Guilt. shame.

819
00:41:44.632 --> 00:41:49.115
floating-on-a-sea-of-vodka
type encounters.

820
00:41:49.158 --> 00:41:53.119
Obviously. I've come
to embrace my sexuality.

821
00:41:53.162 --> 00:41:54.468
Course. you know that.

822
00:41:54.512 --> 00:41:56.470
We met at a gay bar.
didn't we. Daniel?

823
00:41:56.514 --> 00:41:57.732
It was a good place
to score.

824
00:41:57.776 --> 00:42:00.039
I did what I had to.

825
00:42:00.082 --> 00:42:01.780
You've been married?

826
00:42:01.823 --> 00:42:04.043
Twice.

827
00:42:04.086 --> 00:42:07.046
But we're not here for me.
are we?

828
00:42:08.482 --> 00:42:12.007
When you were using drugs.
Mr. Molloy.

829
00:42:12.051 --> 00:42:16.359
do you remember
the best you ever had?

830
00:42:16.403 --> 00:42:18.013
Berkeley. 1978.

831
00:42:18.057 --> 00:42:22.017
Some Mexican black tar that
Carly and Pedro were slinging.

832
00:42:22.061 --> 00:42:25.151
So imagine that

833
00:42:25.194 --> 00:42:27.066
flowing inside
your veins again.

834
00:42:28.633 --> 00:42:33.638
Now multiply it by miles.

835
00:42:33.681 --> 00:42:36.031
to the rings of Saturn
and back.

836
00:42:36.075 --> 00:42:41.602
[Both breathing heavily]

837
00:42:41.646 --> 00:42:45.127
Louis: <i>He had taken what
he called "un petit coup" ...</i>

838
00:42:45.171 --> 00:42:46.868
<i>the little drink.</i>

839
00:42:46.912 --> 00:42:48.653
<i>Not enough to kill me.</i>

840
00:42:48.696 --> 00:42:52.439
<i>but just enough
to keep him fit.</i>

841
00:42:52.482 --> 00:42:56.748
<i>It takes an enormous amount
of restraint for us.</i>

842
00:42:56.791 --> 00:42:58.706
<i>the little drink.</i>

843
00:42:58.750 --> 00:43:02.144
<i>For a human. experiencing it
for the first time.</i>

844
00:43:02.188 --> 00:43:03.972
<i>it was...</i>

845
00:43:04.016 --> 00:43:05.931
<i>unsettling.</i>

846
00:43:05.974 --> 00:43:08.586
<i>And not for the physical toll
on my body.</i>

847
00:43:08.629 --> 00:43:10.631
<i>which was significant.</i>

848
00:43:10.675 --> 00:43:15.201
<i>but for the feelings of
intimacy it awoke within me.</i>

849
00:43:15.244 --> 00:43:17.682
♪

850
00:43:17.725 --> 00:43:20.380
<i>I had never allowed myself</i>

851
00:43:20.423 --> 00:43:22.861
<i>to feel emotionally close
to anyone.</i>

852
00:43:22.904 --> 00:43:24.819
<i>much less a man.</i>

853
00:43:24.863 --> 00:43:28.214
<i>I had no room for feelings
like these in my life.</i>

854
00:43:28.257 --> 00:43:29.824
♪

855
00:43:29.868 --> 00:43:32.958
<i>You could be a lot of things
in New Orleans.</i>

856
00:43:33.001 --> 00:43:38.006
<i>but an openly gay Negro man
was not one of 'em.</i>

857
00:43:38.050 --> 00:43:39.399
[Door opens]

858
00:43:39.442 --> 00:43:42.620
<i>I vowed never to return again.</i>

859
00:43:42.663 --> 00:43:46.014
<i>I shut that night
out of my mind</i>

860
00:43:46.058 --> 00:43:49.714
<i>and turned my attentions back
to life as it was before.</i>

861
00:43:49.757 --> 00:43:51.454
[Door closes]

862
00:43:51.498 --> 00:43:55.589
Crowd:
One. two. three. jump!

863
00:43:55.633 --> 00:43:57.852
[Cheers and applause]

864
00:43:57.896 --> 00:44:04.554
♪

865
00:44:04.598 --> 00:44:11.300
♪

866
00:44:11.344 --> 00:44:12.650
Photographer:
Hold still now.

867
00:44:12.693 --> 00:44:15.217
Grace: We are missing
my father today.

868
00:44:15.261 --> 00:44:17.219
He's supposed to dance with me
to start the night off.

869
00:44:17.263 --> 00:44:18.525
[Flash bulb pops]

870
00:44:18.568 --> 00:44:21.310
I'm trying not to cry now.

871
00:44:21.354 --> 00:44:23.617
And I thought
the best way to honor Daddy

872
00:44:23.661 --> 00:44:25.706
would be to make my brothers
do the work.

873
00:44:25.750 --> 00:44:27.316
Woman: Mm!

874
00:44:27.360 --> 00:44:28.840
Mm-hmm.

875
00:44:28.883 --> 00:44:30.885
Half of y'all
don't know this.

876
00:44:30.929 --> 00:44:35.107
but these no-good boys used to
shuffle for pennies on Sunday.

877
00:44:35.150 --> 00:44:38.153
Called themselves
"The ABCDEFGs".

878
00:44:38.197 --> 00:44:40.503
[Laughter]Remember that. Father Matthias?

879
00:44:40.547 --> 00:44:42.114
Oh. yes.
ABCDE ...

880
00:44:42.157 --> 00:44:43.681
"Alter Boys Come Dancing

881
00:44:43.724 --> 00:44:45.160
Every day For God.""For God."

882
00:44:45.204 --> 00:44:47.032
That's right!

883
00:44:47.075 --> 00:44:48.555
Father Matthias: I remember
their collection hat

884
00:44:48.598 --> 00:44:50.339
didn't always make it
to the collection plate.

885
00:44:50.383 --> 00:44:52.559
That's right.
[Laughs]

886
00:44:52.602 --> 00:44:53.691
Paul. Louis?

887
00:44:53.734 --> 00:44:55.736
Levi: Oh. come on. now.Please!

888
00:44:55.780 --> 00:44:57.738
Hey. now.
Come on. please!

889
00:44:58.870 --> 00:45:01.655
It's for me
on my wedding day.Come on. brother.

890
00:45:01.699 --> 00:45:03.265
[Laughs]

891
00:45:03.309 --> 00:45:05.615
[Groans]
Alright!

892
00:45:05.659 --> 00:45:08.053
[Cheers and applause]

893
00:45:14.407 --> 00:45:15.974
Shoes are tight.

894
00:45:16.017 --> 00:45:18.063
Oh. the shoes is fine.
It's the feet that's fat.

895
00:45:18.106 --> 00:45:19.978
[Laughter]

896
00:45:20.021 --> 00:45:21.762
Hey. what kinda
rhythm you want. boss?

897
00:45:21.806 --> 00:45:24.069
Just play it loud
so they can't hear our feet.

898
00:45:24.112 --> 00:45:26.419
[Laughter]

899
00:45:26.462 --> 00:45:28.682
[Jazz music plays]

900
00:45:28.726 --> 00:45:32.425
Alright.
What you remember?

901
00:45:32.468 --> 00:45:34.296
Um...

902
00:45:34.340 --> 00:45:35.820
♪

903
00:45:35.863 --> 00:45:37.125
Hey. come on.

904
00:45:37.169 --> 00:45:38.736
[Indistinct chatter]

905
00:45:38.779 --> 00:45:40.346
[Laughs]

906
00:45:40.389 --> 00:45:42.696
-Hey!
-Go ahead now!

907
00:45:42.740 --> 00:45:44.306
[Music stops]

908
00:45:44.350 --> 00:45:45.873
[Crowd cheering. whistling]

909
00:45:48.006 --> 00:45:50.443
-Whoo!
-Hey! Hey!

910
00:45:51.792 --> 00:45:53.881
[Cheers and applause]You still got it!

911
00:45:55.535 --> 00:45:57.015
[Shoes tapping rhythmically]

912
00:45:57.058 --> 00:45:59.104
Man: Alright! Okay!

913
00:46:00.975 --> 00:46:03.412
[Music resumes]

914
00:46:03.456 --> 00:46:04.979
They still got it!

915
00:46:05.023 --> 00:46:08.200
[Cheering]

916
00:46:08.243 --> 00:46:09.462
[Tapping continues]

917
00:46:09.505 --> 00:46:11.246
-Oh!
-Yeah. Louis!

918
00:46:11.290 --> 00:46:13.509
[Cheering]

919
00:46:13.553 --> 00:46:15.424
♪

920
00:46:15.468 --> 00:46:18.776
Okay. You ain't gon' do it.
You ain't gon' do it.

921
00:46:19.733 --> 00:46:21.648
[Cheers and applause]

922
00:46:21.691 --> 00:46:31.310
♪

923
00:46:31.353 --> 00:46:33.051
That's right!

924
00:46:33.094 --> 00:46:38.534
♪

925
00:46:38.578 --> 00:46:44.062
♪

926
00:46:44.105 --> 00:46:47.108
[Cheers and applause]

927
00:46:49.154 --> 00:46:50.895
Amazing.

928
00:46:50.938 --> 00:46:53.811
♪

929
00:46:53.854 --> 00:46:56.291
[Applause]

930
00:46:57.510 --> 00:47:04.082
♪

931
00:47:04.125 --> 00:47:06.345
[Dog barking]

932
00:47:06.388 --> 00:47:11.524
♪

933
00:47:11.567 --> 00:47:12.742
We gonna miss it.

934
00:47:12.786 --> 00:47:14.744
Quit talkin'.
I have to concentrate.

935
00:47:15.615 --> 00:47:19.097
It's them three pieces of
chocolate cake holding you back.

936
00:47:19.140 --> 00:47:22.796
Five pieces of chocolate cake.
the Pompano fillet.

937
00:47:22.840 --> 00:47:26.669
three boudins.
dirty rice.

938
00:47:26.713 --> 00:47:30.151
beef. green beans.
five. six wines.

939
00:47:30.195 --> 00:47:32.371
[Groans]
Eat anything else.

940
00:47:32.414 --> 00:47:34.242
the buttons on your vest
gon' pop off

941
00:47:34.286 --> 00:47:35.591
like cannon balls.

942
00:47:35.635 --> 00:47:37.811
take down
the neighborhood.

943
00:47:37.855 --> 00:47:39.421
[Paul groans]

944
00:47:39.465 --> 00:47:46.907
♪

945
00:47:46.951 --> 00:47:50.563
9.517.

946
00:47:50.606 --> 00:47:52.782
That's how many days
we've been in his house.

947
00:47:52.826 --> 00:47:54.741
You do that math
all by yourself?

948
00:47:56.264 --> 00:47:57.613
You remember the day
I got taller than you?

949
00:47:57.657 --> 00:47:58.876
Always bringin'
that up.

950
00:47:58.919 --> 00:48:01.008
Shot up
like a Nuttall oak.

951
00:48:01.052 --> 00:48:03.271
Daddy said I was gon' look down
on you for the rest of days.

952
00:48:03.315 --> 00:48:04.620
Yeah. yeah.

953
00:48:04.664 --> 00:48:05.839
Half an inch.

954
00:48:05.883 --> 00:48:08.015
That was a good month.
that month.

955
00:48:08.059 --> 00:48:12.411
♪

956
00:48:12.454 --> 00:48:14.979
I think you should
get married next.

957
00:48:15.022 --> 00:48:16.328
Do you now?

958
00:48:16.371 --> 00:48:17.633
And you should
marry Hazel.

959
00:48:17.677 --> 00:48:19.809
Hazel? Who that?

960
00:48:19.853 --> 00:48:22.073
The one you were dancing
too close with.

961
00:48:22.116 --> 00:48:24.945
You dance that close.
you ought to be married.

962
00:48:24.989 --> 00:48:27.121
I didn't catch her name.

963
00:48:27.165 --> 00:48:29.254
Well. it's Hazel.

964
00:48:29.297 --> 00:48:32.083
[Church bells toll
in distance]

965
00:48:32.126 --> 00:48:33.780
[Grunts]

966
00:48:36.435 --> 00:48:39.264
You still doing business
with that man Lestat?

967
00:48:40.439 --> 00:48:43.050
Nah.
Didn't work out.

968
00:48:44.834 --> 00:48:47.315
That's good.

969
00:48:47.359 --> 00:48:48.447
'Cause he the Devil.

970
00:48:48.490 --> 00:48:49.796
You think everyone's
the Devil.

971
00:48:49.839 --> 00:48:52.799
He's here to take souls.
He told me so.

972
00:48:52.842 --> 00:48:55.193
He spoke to me
without moving his lips.

973
00:48:55.236 --> 00:48:57.586
He got tricks is all.

974
00:48:58.892 --> 00:49:01.242
Mortal sins
must be confessed. Louis.

975
00:49:01.286 --> 00:49:04.202
Ain't never gon' see him again.
Paul.

976
00:49:08.989 --> 00:49:11.122
You think Levi
loves her enough?

977
00:49:11.165 --> 00:49:13.863
You know.
Grace needs a lot of love.

978
00:49:13.907 --> 00:49:15.343
I do.

979
00:49:16.388 --> 00:49:19.652
Do you think he's givin' her
everything he's got inside him?

980
00:49:21.001 --> 00:49:22.133
Mm-hmm.

981
00:49:25.963 --> 00:49:29.879
♪

982
00:49:29.923 --> 00:49:32.056
Mother made a good party
for Grace.

983
00:49:32.099 --> 00:49:33.622
Mm-hmm. yeah.

984
00:49:33.666 --> 00:49:35.624
Yeah. they gon' talk about
this one for years.

985
00:49:35.668 --> 00:49:37.235
Yeah.

986
00:49:37.278 --> 00:49:43.328
♪

987
00:49:43.371 --> 00:49:44.938
I love you. Louis.

988
00:49:44.982 --> 00:49:46.853
And I love you. too.
baby brother.

989
00:49:46.896 --> 00:49:54.165
♪

990
00:49:54.208 --> 00:49:56.950
I ate too much
chocolate cake.

991
00:49:56.994 --> 00:50:01.041
♪

992
00:50:01.085 --> 00:50:02.260
Paul.

993
00:50:02.303 --> 00:50:04.218
♪

994
00:50:04.262 --> 00:50:05.654
Paul!

995
00:50:06.742 --> 00:50:08.135
[Thud]

996
00:50:08.179 --> 00:50:09.267
Paul!

997
00:50:09.310 --> 00:50:10.659
[Woman gasping]

998
00:50:10.703 --> 00:50:12.922
Man: Oh. my lord!Woman: Paul!

999
00:50:12.966 --> 00:50:15.490
♪

1000
00:50:15.534 --> 00:50:17.927
That was the last sunrise
I ever saw.

1001
00:50:19.320 --> 00:50:22.149
Perhaps the kindest thing
the dark gift has given me.

1002
00:50:22.193 --> 00:50:27.328
♪

1003
00:50:27.372 --> 00:50:30.810
I don't miss the sun.

1004
00:50:30.853 --> 00:50:32.638
the reminders it carries.

1005
00:50:32.681 --> 00:50:39.427
♪

1006
00:50:39.471 --> 00:50:46.260
♪

1007
00:50:46.304 --> 00:50:53.050
♪

1008
00:50:53.093 --> 00:50:56.618
I have seen death
over and over

1009
00:50:56.662 --> 00:50:59.882
and over and over again.

1010
00:51:00.927 --> 00:51:02.624
It's boring.

1011
00:51:02.668 --> 00:51:04.844
That'll make
a great blurb.

1012
00:51:04.887 --> 00:51:07.586
The diagnosis you received.
Daniel.

1013
00:51:07.629 --> 00:51:10.632
it winds your clock.

1014
00:51:10.676 --> 00:51:12.852
This virus has turned
the world sideways.

1015
00:51:12.895 --> 00:51:14.332
I get it.

1016
00:51:14.375 --> 00:51:15.594
I'm gonna die.

1017
00:51:15.637 --> 00:51:17.770
They're gonna die.

1018
00:51:17.813 --> 00:51:19.206
But not the vampire.

1019
00:51:19.250 --> 00:51:21.513
The vampire is bored.

1020
00:51:23.080 --> 00:51:25.430
The human was destroyed.

1021
00:51:26.996 --> 00:51:29.825
Utterly destroyed.

1022
00:51:29.869 --> 00:51:31.566
Father Matthias:
I was at the funeral home.

1023
00:51:31.610 --> 00:51:33.612
Everything is going
as it should.

1024
00:51:33.655 --> 00:51:37.094
Good men there.
Promised me that ...

1025
00:51:37.137 --> 00:51:39.139
You musta said something
to him. Louis.

1026
00:51:39.183 --> 00:51:40.880
You musta said
something to him

1027
00:51:40.923 --> 00:51:43.274
to make him do that
to himself.

1028
00:51:44.492 --> 00:51:47.452
Paul slipped and fell.
Florence.

1029
00:51:47.495 --> 00:51:49.236
I don't think this is something
you want to pursue.

1030
00:51:49.280 --> 00:51:52.326
He was a fragile boy.

1031
00:51:52.370 --> 00:51:54.241
He always was.

1032
00:51:56.548 --> 00:51:59.986
And you. you always had
to have the last word.

1033
00:52:00.029 --> 00:52:01.422
didn't you. Louis?

1034
00:52:01.466 --> 00:52:03.250
You always had to take him
down a peg.

1035
00:52:03.294 --> 00:52:05.861
Mamaw.

1036
00:52:05.905 --> 00:52:07.776
What did you say
to him?

1037
00:52:07.820 --> 00:52:09.648
Why was you
even up there?

1038
00:52:10.692 --> 00:52:13.434
Watchin' the sun come up.
Mama.

1039
00:52:13.478 --> 00:52:16.437
[Sighs]

1040
00:52:16.481 --> 00:52:21.007
You don't get past the gates
iffen you kill yourself.

1041
00:52:21.050 --> 00:52:23.488
Don't you know that?

1042
00:52:23.531 --> 00:52:26.882
Paul gone down
the other way.

1043
00:52:26.926 --> 00:52:29.494
Paul's in Hell
because of you.

1044
00:52:42.550 --> 00:52:44.987
Louis:
Storyville lowered their hats.

1045
00:52:45.031 --> 00:52:48.295
gave their propers.
because it was custom.

1046
00:52:48.339 --> 00:52:50.993
But if you look past
those lined up on the sidewalks.

1047
00:52:51.037 --> 00:52:53.648
you'd see the bars
hadn't stopped serving.

1048
00:52:53.692 --> 00:52:56.129
the whores
hadn't stopped whoring.

1049
00:52:56.173 --> 00:52:58.000
What was Paul's life
worth to them?

1050
00:52:58.044 --> 00:53:00.133
What was <i>my</i>life worth?

1051
00:53:00.177 --> 00:53:02.353
The big man of Liberty Street.

1052
00:53:02.396 --> 00:53:06.705
trailing the satin-lined
evidence of his failure.

1053
00:53:06.748 --> 00:53:09.360
Easy prey
for the discerning predator.

1054
00:53:13.712 --> 00:53:16.018
An elegant coffin. Would you
tell me where you purchased ...

1055
00:53:16.062 --> 00:53:17.194
Move on.

1056
00:53:17.237 --> 00:53:18.891
I wait on my balcony
every night.

1057
00:53:18.934 --> 00:53:20.806
You've been avoiding me.I have been occupied.

1058
00:53:20.849 --> 00:53:23.417
Miss Lily proved herself
a poor substitute.

1059
00:53:23.461 --> 00:53:25.245
And I don't take kindly
to being avoided.

1060
00:53:25.289 --> 00:53:26.333
It's my brother's
funeral!

1061
00:53:26.377 --> 00:53:27.900
Believe me
when I tell you.

1062
00:53:27.943 --> 00:53:29.597
your brother longed
for that flagstone.

1063
00:53:29.641 --> 00:53:31.338
What'd you say to me?!

1064
00:53:31.382 --> 00:53:33.775
I got it. boss.
Keep walking.

1065
00:53:33.819 --> 00:53:36.213
♪

1066
00:53:36.256 --> 00:53:38.563
[Groans]

1067
00:53:38.606 --> 00:53:41.740
♪

1068
00:53:41.783 --> 00:53:45.613
Louis: <i>Lestat's ambush
had disoriented me.</i>

1069
00:53:45.657 --> 00:53:48.486
<i>The sermon that was given.
I could not hear.</i>

1070
00:53:50.139 --> 00:53:53.099
<i>And when the gathering
cut loose the body.</i>

1071
00:53:53.142 --> 00:53:54.840
<i>I could not join
the transformation</i>

1072
00:53:54.883 --> 00:53:58.191
<i>of those in attendance.</i>

1073
00:53:58.235 --> 00:54:01.716
<i>He would not let me.</i>

1074
00:54:01.760 --> 00:54:02.935
Lestat: <i>Come to me.</i>

1075
00:54:05.372 --> 00:54:06.417
<i>Come to me.</i>

1076
00:54:07.461 --> 00:54:08.462
No.

1077
00:54:08.506 --> 00:54:16.078
♪

1078
00:54:16.122 --> 00:54:17.863
Walk you home. Mama?

1079
00:54:17.906 --> 00:54:20.300
No. thank you.

1080
00:54:20.344 --> 00:54:22.259
Levi.
do you mind?

1081
00:54:23.912 --> 00:54:25.914
Of course.
Mama Du Lac.

1082
00:54:29.701 --> 00:54:30.919
She didn't mean
nothin' by it.

1083
00:54:30.963 --> 00:54:32.138
Oh. but she did now.

1084
00:54:32.181 --> 00:54:34.619
She just needs
to put it somewhere.

1085
00:54:35.663 --> 00:54:37.056
Don't let it inside.

1086
00:54:39.798 --> 00:54:41.452
[Smooches]

1087
00:54:41.495 --> 00:54:43.628
See you back at the wake?

1088
00:54:43.671 --> 00:54:49.024
♪

1089
00:54:49.068 --> 00:54:50.635
<i>Come to me.</i>

1090
00:54:51.984 --> 00:54:54.465
Louis:
<i>I did not go to the wake.</i>

1091
00:54:56.249 --> 00:54:59.470
<i>I did not want to face
my mother's blame...</i>

1092
00:54:59.513 --> 00:55:01.559
[Thunder crashes]

1093
00:55:01.602 --> 00:55:03.474
<i>...my sister's pity.</i>

1094
00:55:04.736 --> 00:55:07.173
<i>I wanted to grieve alone.</i>

1095
00:55:09.088 --> 00:55:13.005
<i>But he would not allow it.</i>

1096
00:55:15.703 --> 00:55:17.401
Lestat:
<i>Come to me. Louis.</i>

1097
00:55:20.491 --> 00:55:22.188
<i>Come to me.</i>

1098
00:55:22.231 --> 00:55:27.889
♪

1099
00:55:27.933 --> 00:55:28.977
Hello. handsome.

1100
00:55:29.021 --> 00:55:30.631
Sazerac.

1101
00:55:30.675 --> 00:55:33.286
My heart broke when I heard
of your brother's passing.

1102
00:55:33.330 --> 00:55:34.809
Miss Lily.

1103
00:55:34.853 --> 00:55:36.289
Oh. my dear.

1104
00:55:36.333 --> 00:55:37.638
I don't care if she busy
with someone.

1105
00:55:37.682 --> 00:55:39.205
I'll pay more.

1106
00:55:39.248 --> 00:55:41.686
'Cause I like Miss Lily.
and I need Miss Lily.

1107
00:55:41.729 --> 00:55:43.992
Miss Lily died.
Mr. du Lac.

1108
00:55:45.516 --> 00:55:46.865
Two weeks ago.

1109
00:55:46.908 --> 00:55:48.954
[Table clatters]

1110
00:55:48.997 --> 00:55:51.957
Police found her
under the docks.

1111
00:55:52.000 --> 00:55:55.830
Said she contracted the fevers
that's been going around.

1112
00:55:55.874 --> 00:55:58.572
Blood went and dried up
inside her.

1113
00:55:58.616 --> 00:55:59.878
<i>Viens à moi.</i>

1114
00:56:01.270 --> 00:56:02.707
[Pounding on door]

1115
00:56:02.750 --> 00:56:05.492
Louis:
Father! Father Matthias!

1116
00:56:05.536 --> 00:56:06.798
Help me!

1117
00:56:06.841 --> 00:56:08.582
[Pounding continues]

1118
00:56:08.626 --> 00:56:12.151
Help me. please.
He's in my head. Father.

1119
00:56:14.240 --> 00:56:16.982
The Devil
is in New Orleans.

1120
00:56:17.025 --> 00:56:18.244
Father Matthias:
Calm down. son.

1121
00:56:18.287 --> 00:56:19.332
Catch your breath.

1122
00:56:19.376 --> 00:56:21.073
[Panting]

1123
00:56:21.116 --> 00:56:23.902
Bless me. Father.
f-for I have sinned.

1124
00:56:23.945 --> 00:56:26.470
Grievously sinned.

1125
00:56:26.513 --> 00:56:28.341
Sign of the cross. son.

1126
00:56:28.385 --> 00:56:34.260
♪

1127
00:56:34.303 --> 00:56:37.611
[Breathing raggedly]

1128
00:56:37.655 --> 00:56:39.047
I'm a drunk. Lord.

1129
00:56:39.091 --> 00:56:40.484
I'm a liar.

1130
00:56:40.527 --> 00:56:41.920
I am a thief. Lord.

1131
00:56:41.963 --> 00:56:43.791
I profit off the miseries
of other men.

1132
00:56:43.835 --> 00:56:44.923
and I do it easy.

1133
00:56:44.966 --> 00:56:47.229
Drugs. liquor. women.

1134
00:56:47.273 --> 00:56:50.102
I-I-I-I lure them in
and grab what they got. Lord.

1135
00:56:50.145 --> 00:56:51.973
I take daughters
with no homes

1136
00:56:52.017 --> 00:56:55.542
and I-I put 'em out
on the street. Lord.

1137
00:56:55.586 --> 00:56:58.327
and I lie to myself.
saying I-I'm giving them a roof

1138
00:56:58.371 --> 00:57:00.112
and food and dollar bills
in they pocket.

1139
00:57:00.155 --> 00:57:02.549
but I look in the mirror.
I know what I am ...

1140
00:57:02.593 --> 00:57:04.377
the big man
in the big house.

1141
00:57:04.421 --> 00:57:07.380
stuffing cotton in my ears
so I can't hear their cries.

1142
00:57:07.424 --> 00:57:10.601
And Lord. I dragged my family
into this mess with me.

1143
00:57:11.689 --> 00:57:14.779
I shame my father.

1144
00:57:14.822 --> 00:57:16.433
I f... I failed my brother.

1145
00:57:16.476 --> 00:57:17.608
No. son.

1146
00:57:17.651 --> 00:57:20.349
I lost my mother
and sister.

1147
00:57:20.393 --> 00:57:23.483
and rather than fix it
like a man should. Lord.

1148
00:57:23.527 --> 00:57:25.833
I run like a coward.

1149
00:57:25.877 --> 00:57:27.705
I run to the bottle.

1150
00:57:27.748 --> 00:57:28.967
I run to the grift.

1151
00:57:29.010 --> 00:57:31.186
I run to bad beds.

1152
00:57:31.230 --> 00:57:33.711
I-I laid down
with a man.

1153
00:57:33.754 --> 00:57:35.452
[Thunder rumbles]

1154
00:57:35.495 --> 00:57:38.150
I laid down
with the Devil.

1155
00:57:38.193 --> 00:57:40.935
And he has roots in me.

1156
00:57:40.979 --> 00:57:44.417
all his spindly roots
in me.

1157
00:57:44.461 --> 00:57:47.246
and I can't think
nothin' anymore

1158
00:57:47.289 --> 00:57:50.423
but his voice
and his words!

1159
00:57:50.467 --> 00:57:52.686
[Door opens]Please. help me!

1160
00:57:52.730 --> 00:57:54.819
[Metal clatters]I am weak!

1161
00:57:54.862 --> 00:57:56.342
[Thunder rumbles]

1162
00:57:56.385 --> 00:57:58.170
I wanna die!

1163
00:57:58.213 --> 00:58:00.520
[Rattling]

1164
00:58:00.564 --> 00:58:02.000
Oh!

1165
00:58:02.043 --> 00:58:04.350
[Crashing]

1166
00:58:04.393 --> 00:58:07.005
[Screams]

1167
00:58:08.310 --> 00:58:10.095
[Flesh tearing]

1168
00:58:10.138 --> 00:58:11.313
[Crack]

1169
00:58:11.357 --> 00:58:13.751
[Muffled groan]

1170
00:58:13.794 --> 00:58:17.711
♪

1171
00:58:17.755 --> 00:58:20.322
[Breathing heavily]

1172
00:58:20.366 --> 00:58:22.368
No!

1173
00:58:22.411 --> 00:58:25.980
♪

1174
00:58:26.024 --> 00:58:28.330
Do you think God
heard you. Louis.

1175
00:58:28.374 --> 00:58:31.986
in that tawdry box.
through this pig vessel.

1176
00:58:32.030 --> 00:58:34.511
this ... this charlatan?

1177
00:58:36.208 --> 00:58:39.080
Do you not see
how unworthy he is?

1178
00:58:39.124 --> 00:58:41.692
How can you humiliate yourself
like this?!

1179
00:58:41.735 --> 00:58:43.607
[Groans]

1180
00:58:43.650 --> 00:58:45.565
[Thunder rumbles]

1181
00:58:45.609 --> 00:58:49.264
♪

1182
00:58:49.308 --> 00:58:51.702
[Breathing heavily]

1183
00:58:51.745 --> 00:58:53.834
You killed Lily.

1184
00:58:53.878 --> 00:58:57.011
Cut short that magnificent
life she was living.

1185
00:58:57.055 --> 00:58:58.752
What a tragedy.

1186
00:58:58.796 --> 00:59:01.581
Ain't no fever out there.
That's you.

1187
00:59:01.625 --> 00:59:03.540
You bringin' the death
to town.

1188
00:59:03.583 --> 00:59:05.193
I give death
to those deserving.

1189
00:59:05.237 --> 00:59:07.935
[Thunder rumbles]

1190
00:59:07.979 --> 00:59:09.850
I'm not the Devil.

1191
00:59:09.894 --> 00:59:11.722
You were wrong
about that.

1192
00:59:13.245 --> 00:59:14.507
But I can give you death.

1193
00:59:14.551 --> 00:59:15.987
[Shoe squeaks]

1194
00:59:16.030 --> 00:59:18.119
[Thunder crashes]

1195
00:59:18.163 --> 00:59:23.516
♪

1196
00:59:23.560 --> 00:59:24.517
[Gasps]

1197
00:59:24.561 --> 00:59:25.736
♪

1198
00:59:25.779 --> 00:59:27.259
[Whimpers. grunts]

1199
00:59:27.302 --> 00:59:31.829
♪

1200
00:59:31.872 --> 00:59:35.006
[Footsteps echoing]

1201
00:59:35.049 --> 00:59:44.711
♪

1202
00:59:44.755 --> 00:59:54.460
♪

1203
00:59:54.503 --> 01:00:04.165
♪

1204
01:00:04.209 --> 01:00:07.299
[Breathing heavily]

1205
01:00:07.342 --> 01:00:10.215
This primitive country
has picked you clean.

1206
01:00:10.258 --> 01:00:14.654
It has shackled you
in permanent exile.

1207
01:00:14.698 --> 01:00:16.525
Every room you enter.

1208
01:00:16.569 --> 01:00:18.353
every hat you are forced
to wear ...

1209
01:00:18.397 --> 01:00:20.878
the stern landlord.
the deferential businessman.

1210
01:00:20.921 --> 01:00:22.270
the loyal son ...

1211
01:00:22.314 --> 01:00:24.272
all these roles
you conform to

1212
01:00:24.316 --> 01:00:26.797
and none of them
your true nature.

1213
01:00:26.840 --> 01:00:28.450
[Thunder crashes]

1214
01:00:28.494 --> 01:00:31.889
What rage you must feel
as you choke on your sorrow.

1215
01:00:34.631 --> 01:00:36.981
The first time
I laid eyes on you.

1216
01:00:37.024 --> 01:00:38.852
your beautiful face.

1217
01:00:38.896 --> 01:00:41.376
I saw that sorrow.

1218
01:00:41.420 --> 01:00:42.726
I did not know
how it got there

1219
01:00:42.769 --> 01:00:45.642
or why
it was so voluminous.

1220
01:00:48.383 --> 01:00:51.648
I can take away
that sorrow. Louis.

1221
01:00:52.823 --> 01:00:55.303
I can give you that death

1222
01:00:55.347 --> 01:00:58.698
you begged your feeble.
blind. degenerate.

1223
01:00:58.742 --> 01:01:02.702
nonexistent god for.

1224
01:01:02.746 --> 01:01:05.836
But I can do it...

1225
01:01:05.879 --> 01:01:07.794
joyfully.

1226
01:01:09.274 --> 01:01:12.843
I can swap
this life of shame.

1227
01:01:12.886 --> 01:01:15.410
swap it out
for a dark gift

1228
01:01:15.454 --> 01:01:18.196
and a power
you can't begin to imagine.

1229
01:01:20.720 --> 01:01:22.679
You just have
to ask me for it.

1230
01:01:24.811 --> 01:01:28.728
You just have to nod
your beautiful head...

1231
01:01:28.772 --> 01:01:30.382
and say yes.

1232
01:01:30.425 --> 01:01:34.386
♪

1233
01:01:34.429 --> 01:01:36.214
I love you. Louis.

1234
01:01:37.824 --> 01:01:39.696
You are loved.

1235
01:01:41.610 --> 01:01:44.222
I send my love to you.

1236
01:01:44.265 --> 01:01:47.965
and you send it back
round to me.

1237
01:01:48.008 --> 01:01:51.055
And this circle.

1238
01:01:51.098 --> 01:01:54.406
this home we barely had
a glimpse of...

1239
01:01:57.278 --> 01:01:59.846
...know it frightens me
as much as it does you.

1240
01:01:59.890 --> 01:02:02.457
Louis:
<i>It is difficult to explain</i>

1241
01:02:02.501 --> 01:02:05.591
<i>how his words disarmed me.</i>

1242
01:02:05.634 --> 01:02:09.290
<i>how efficiently succinct
and impenetrable</i>

1243
01:02:09.334 --> 01:02:11.336
<i>his argument was.</i>

1244
01:02:11.379 --> 01:02:13.251
<i>All my conceptions.</i>

1245
01:02:13.294 --> 01:02:16.341
<i>even my guilt
and my wish to die</i>

1246
01:02:16.384 --> 01:02:19.083
<i>seemed utterly unimportant.</i>

1247
01:02:19.126 --> 01:02:21.302
<i>and I completely forgot myself</i>

1248
01:02:21.346 --> 01:02:25.089
<i>and the barbaric scene
that surrounded me.</i>

1249
01:02:25.132 --> 01:02:30.790
<i>For the first time in my life.
I was seen.</i>

1250
01:02:30.834 --> 01:02:33.880
Be my companion.
Louis.

1251
01:02:35.229 --> 01:02:39.233
Be all the beautiful things
you are.

1252
01:02:39.277 --> 01:02:41.366
and be them without apology.

1253
01:02:43.672 --> 01:02:45.370
For all eternity.

1254
01:02:45.413 --> 01:02:53.987
♪

1255
01:02:54.031 --> 01:03:02.691
♪

1256
01:03:02.735 --> 01:03:07.914
<i>He drained me
to the very threshold of death.</i>

1257
01:03:07.958 --> 01:03:13.398
♪

1258
01:03:13.441 --> 01:03:14.442
[Groans]

1259
01:03:14.486 --> 01:03:16.227
Mm.

1260
01:03:16.270 --> 01:03:20.144
♪

1261
01:03:20.187 --> 01:03:22.886
